16/01/2006
IOANNINA, Greece -- Deputy Foreign Minister Evripides Stylianidis has reaffirmed his country's support for Albania's EU integration bid. During talks with representatives of the ethnic Greek community in Albania on Sunday (15 January), Stylianidis said Greek assistance to Albania totalled 184m euros in the past four years.
Also at the weekend, Albanian Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli called for a meeting between Prime Minister Sali Berisha, leader of the ruling Democratic Party, and Edi Rama, mayor of Tirana and head of the main opposition Socialists. She urged them to overcome their differences over a road construction project in Tirana and to focus on crucial electoral reforms. (Albanian News - 16/01/06; ANA - 15/01/06)
